{"title":"The Sky Was Purple and Red and Yellow and On Fire","link":"https://kottke.org/24/05/the-sky-was-purple-and-red-and-yellow-and-on-fire","date":1715561082000,"content":"\n        <p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/aurora-solar-storm-01.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/aurora-solar-storm-01.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/aurora-solar-storm-01.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"1165\" alt=\"a photo of the aurora borealis above windmills\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/aurora-solar-storm-02.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/aurora-solar-storm-02.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/aurora-solar-storm-02.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"865\" alt=\"a photo of the aurora borealis above some mountains\" /></p>\n\n<p>There was <a href=\"https://www.space.com/solar-storm-coronal-mass-ejections-mothers-day-weekend-storm-watch\">a big solar storm</a> this weekend and photos of the aurora borealis took over social media; it was delightful. For round-ups, check out <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/05/10/world/europe/aurora-northern-lights-solar-storm-photos.html?unlocked_article_code=1.rk0.lQsr.9thJirFNKv53\">the NY Times</a>, <a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/science/gallery/2024/may/11/northern-lights-aurora-borealis-skies-us-canada-in-pictures\">the Guardian</a>, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/itsjackcohen/status/1789290289246490912\">@itsjackcohen</a>, <a href=\"https://www.pbs.org/newshour/science/photos-solar-storm-produces-dazzling-northern-lights-in-northern-hemisphere\">PBS NewsHour</a>, <a href=\"https://spaceweathergallery2.com/index.php?title=aurora\">Spaceweather.com</a>, <a href=\"https://www.forbes.com/sites/jamiecartereurope/2024/05/11/in-photos-aurora-seen-across-the-world-in-very-rare-sky-show/\">Forbes</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.msn.com/en-us/weather/topstories/best-photos-of-friday-s-stunning-aurora-borealis-seen-across-the-us/ss-BB1megjp\">MSN</a>.</p>\n\n<p>The photos above are by <a href=\"https://www.albertdros.com/?pgid=iqjiwjij-545d06cd-f555-4c96-bde4-2e2ba927638c\">Albert Dros</a> and <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/C6z07_QvyaE/\">Sean Oâ€™ Riordan</a> (<a href=\"https://www.seanoriordanphotography.com/shop/1xs8a14hztfz9t9nx75gfgpr8pm1at\">prints here</a>). Oâ€™ Riordan took his shot in Tasmania and actually had to tone it down for publication:</p>\n\n<blockquote><p>When the clouds are glowing red you know something is off the charts, I tried my best to desaturate this and make it look some bit like a photo and not a science fiction scene!</p></blockquote>\n\n        \n\n         <p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/astronomy\">astronomy</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/photography\">photography</a></p>\n\n         <p>ðŸ’¬ <a href=\"https://kottke.org/24/05/the-sky-was-purple-and-red-and-yellow-and-on-fire\">Join the discussion on kottke.org</a> â†’</p>\n\n    ","author":"Jason Kottke","siteTitle":"Kottke","siteHash":"89a883271b4598f9b33ebe87be70d38557bcd266e68aee521a8f93622e0ab723","entryHash":"8981346a1941324dc5bf0156c3baa6944132614d91e5931e3194b944d82fbc7d","category":"default"}